homeDescription: This exquisitely restored Victorian Eastlake Historic home features 6+ bedrooms,4 working fireplaces and 2.5 baths and is conveniently located two short blocks from the Fanwood Train Station. The home has been extensively restored from top to bottom. The open front porch provides a wonderful outdoor entertaining space. Sip lemonade and watch the holiday parade pass by. Once inside, the sweeping Reception Hall welcomes guests with it's lovely Italian Marble fireplace and stunning chandelier. The staircase to the second floor is a beautiful reminder of the home's history. The Side Hall features an exterior door, coat closet and Powder Room.The Formal Parlor is a true "gem box" with incredibly intricate wall coverings, stained glass windows and marble (gas) fireplace.The Living Room is enormous, and has a tiled fireplace and lovely tin ceiling. There are two sets of impressive double doors that lead back to the Reception hall.The Dining Room boasts yet another working fireplace and two Butler's closets. The Kitchen is large, bright and airy, and features a servants staircase to the second floor. There is also a door to the fenced in yard.The Second Floor is home to 5 bedrooms plus a small Nursery attached to the Master Bedroom (future master bath?). The Main Bath is stunning, with stained glass window, high tank toilet and double sinks. The Laundry is tucked into a convenient Hall location... perfect for family living.The Third Floor includes one finished bedroom, plus an unfinished room, cedar storage room, and a massive storage area that has great potential for expansion.Down in the Basement, the surprises continue...there is a large work area, and a finished Rec Room. A full Bath completes this area. The beauty of this home is unparallelled. Incredible attention to detail and a true respect for history, has returned this home to it's former splendor! This home is on the National Register of Historic Places.

homeDescription: Expanded cape. Beautiful Curb appeal in the front back and both sides.  the grounds are kept up beautifully. Off the kitchen there is a screened in porch that we use about 10 months a year.  there are 2 doors off of the porch, 1 to the garage, and one to our L shaped deck, 33ft x 12ft deck, and an extra 90 sq feet on top of that.  New windows, new bathrooms, new roof, new furnace, new hot water heater, hardwood floors, newly renovated kitchen. Central air and gas heat, brand new front porch with new railings.
